@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{org-web-tools-extras.el} extends @samp{org-web-tools}, the package that provides utilities for interacting with web content within Org mode. The upstream package offers commands for inserting Org-formatted links and reading web pages, but some of these are designed for interactive use and do not integrate smoothly with programmatic contexts such as Org Capture templates.

@samp{org-web-tools-extras.el} addresses this gap with two focused functions:

@itemize
@item
@strong{Link insertion from the kill ring.} A function that fetches the title for a URL found in the kill ring and returns a formatted Org link, suitable for use in Org Capture templates (@ref{Inserting a link from the clipboard}).
@item
@strong{Title extraction.} A function that fetches and returns just the title of a web page at a given URL, using the @samp{plz} HTTP library for retrieval (@ref{Extracting a page title}).
@end itemize

The package depends on @samp{org-web-tools} and @samp{paths}.

